Defendant Jermaine E Washington in court with attorney Paul A. Oberer.  Defendant Jermaine E Washington in custody.  William T. Berens appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.

The Court imposed the following sentence:   

AS TO COUNT #7:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be SEVEN (7) years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for TWO (2) years with credit for 148 days time served.  Defendant shall serve FIVE (5) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

AS TO COUNT #15:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be SEVEN (7) years CONCURRENT to Count #7.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for TWO (2) years with credit for 148 days time served.  Defendant shall serve FIVE (5) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

AS TO COUNT #19:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be FOUR (4) years CONCURRENT to Count #15.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for TWO (2) years with credit for 148 days time served.  Defendant shall serve two (2) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant.

AS TO COUNTS #7, #15 AND #19:
CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Practice Absolute Sobriety;
 - No use, possession or sale/delivery of illegal drugs or possession of drug paraphernalia;
  - Seek and maintain employment and/or school AT LEAST 40 hours a week;
 - 25 hours of Community Service in the Sherman Park area.  Not near the victims or co-actors (E.W. and Owens)
 - No contact with co-actors (E.W. and Owens) or victims.
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements is secondary to restitution.
 - Restitution of $300.00 to Fay H.; $1,100 to Medford R.; and $1,045 to the Pame V.  Court ordered monies taken by the Department of Correction from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance would then be paid while on Extended Supervision. 

